videos.description: Malik Rosier throws a quick screen to Travis Homer who has an open field in front of him and collects 25 yards.
videos.headline: Screen pass turns into  25-yard gain for Miami

videos.description: Malik Rosier throws a perfect pass to the corner of the end zone for Braxton Berrios who is able to hang on and get one foot down for Miami to take the lead.
videos.headline: Rosier drops in a dime for the TD

videos.description: Jaquan Johnson keeps his eyes on the deflected pass and is able to come down with the interception to give Miami great field position.
videos.headline: Miami dawns the turnover chain after INT

videos.description: Malik Rosier now has a rushing touchdown and a passing touchdown in the first quarter.
videos.headline: Rosier hustles in for the rushing TD

videos.description: Brandon Wimbush sails a pass and Miami's Malek Young jumps up to grab the interception and take ownership of the Turnover Chain.
videos.headline: The Turnover Chain has a new owner

videos.description: After two interceptions by starting QB Brandon Wimbush, the Irish insert Ian Book into the game.
videos.headline: Notre Dame has a new QB

videos.description: True Freshman Trajan Bandy reads the pass from Ian Book and takes it 65 yards to the house to give the Hurricanes a big halftime lead.
videos.headline: Pick-6 makes the Turnover Chain shine brighter

videos.description: Miami head coach Mark Richt is pleased with the production on the defensive side of the ball, but doesn't want to forget the two offensive touchdowns.
videos.headline: Richt on Miami's D: 'They're doing awesome'

videos.description: The offensive struggles for the Irish warranted the QB change, so head coach Brian Kelly wants to clean up the offense in the second half.
videos.headline: Notre Dame coach Kelly: 'Let's fight'

videos.description: Malik Rosier has a score in the air and on the ground, as Miami's defense holds Notre Dame scoreless in the first half and cruises to a 41-8 victory.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Miami shuts down ND) 2017/11/11 SOTFULL ESHEET

videos.headline: Miami shuts down ND

videos.description: Travis Homer finds a hole and takes off for a 40-yard gain.
videos.headline: Homer breaks free for 40 yards

videos.description: Lawrence Cager climbs the ladder and pulls down an impressive catch to convert on fourth down and get the Hurricanes inside the Notre Dame 10-yard line.
videos.headline: Miami converts on fourth with great catch

videos.description: DeeJay Dallas turns the corner and soars over the pylon for his first career touchdown.
videos.headline: Canes with another rushing TD

videos.description: Brandon Wimbush throws a perfectly placed ball to Alize Mack who jumps up for the touchdown.
videos.headline: Notre Dame scores on leaping TD catch

videos.description: Jonathan Garvin comes flying around the corner and knocks the ball out of Brandon Wimbush's hand and recovers for the strip sack.
videos.headline: Miami with 4th takeaway on fumble recovery

videos.description: DeeJay Dallas gets the call on fourth-and-goal and stretches over the goal line for his second touchdown of the game.
videos.headline: Miami capitalizes on turnover with rushing TD

videos.description: Miami head coach Mark Richt talks about the dominant performance against Notre Dame and a berth in the ACC Championship Game.
videos.headline: Richt on Miami's Coastal title: 'It's a big deal'

videos.description: Miami QB Malik Rosier said his job was made easy when the defense put up a strong showing.
videos.headline: Rosier says defense is playing phenomenally

videos.description: Chris Fowler and Kirk Herbstreit break down Miami's impressive performance on both sides of the ball as the Hurricanes push for the College Football Playoff.
videos.headline: Miami puts a beatdown on Notre Dame

videos.description: Miami forces four Notre Dame turnovers and Malik Rosier throws for 137 yards and accounts for two touchdowns, one in the air and one on the ground, as the Hurricanes defeat the Fighting Irish 41-8.
videos.headline: Miami dominates Notre Dame

videos.description: The Turnover Chain kept changing hands as Miami's defensive dominated with four turnovers, including a pick-6, en route to a 41-8 win.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Turnover Chain lit against Irish) 2017/11/11 ESHEET ENHL

videos.headline: Turnover Chain lit against Irish

videos.description: The Hurricanes barge into the playoff picture with an emphatic win over the Fighting Irish, and their fans couldn't be more hyped.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Dominance of The U leaves Miami buzzing) 2017/11/11 ESHEET ENHL

videos.headline: Dominance of The U leaves Miami buzzing
